cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with the application of online dictionary learning (ODL) technique for target recognition in ground penetration radar (GPR) signals. This involves feature extraction and classification, which are common tasks in computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, ODL is a type of neural network (NN) that learns from data, making cs.NE a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions compressed sensing (CS) techniques for faster data acquisition, which falls under cs.MM. Finally, the paper discusses the use of learned dictionaries for cognitive operation of the GPR, which involves information retrieval (IR) and decision making, making cs.IR a possible sub-category.
